Service awards are a simple way of acknowledging an editor's level of contribution to the PG&E Wiki.

It is achieved by a strictly mechanical count of your number of edits which includes all changes you make to the Wiki (edits, new page creation, file updates, new files, etc.). The Wiki [[Template:Service awards|automatically determines]] your edits and displays the correct badge, if you do not want this to show up on your userpage, remove the template <code><nowiki>{{Service awards}}</nowiki></code> from your userpage.

